Enum Class OpCode

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<OpCode>
common.OpCode
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<OpCode>, Constable
public enum OpCode extends Enum<OpCode>
Defines all operation codes used in client-server communication.

OpCode is the system-wide "protocol dictionary": every message sent between the client and the server uses one value from this enum to indicate the requested action and the expected response type.

Naming Convention
  • REQUEST_* - Sent from client to server to ask for an operation.
  • RESPONSE_* - Sent from server to client as a reply to a request.
  • INFO / ERROR - General messages not tied to a specific request/response pair.

In this project, OpCode is typically wrapped inside Envelope and transmitted over the network (often serialized using KryoUtil). Both client and server must share the same enum definition to remain compatible.
